Pleasant Grove Elementary School
May 5 at 5:26 PM ¬∑

I have completed the task of walking every neighborhood in the Pleasant Grove district - One hundred sixty one point seven (161.7) miles! Unfortunately I didn't take my phone on my first couple of walks and don't have pictures, so I am sorry. I hope to continue this activity throughout the summer, as it has brought so much joy to my heart. I hope it has done the same for the PGES families. I look forward to the time where we can all be together - IN SCHOOL. I can't thank you enough for the messages, chalk drawings, waters, waves, and so much more - we have a special community. Proud to be a Pleasant Grove Panther!

post_text:
Center Grove is partnering with the IMPACT Center at Mount Pleasant Christian Church, 381 N Bluff Rd, Greenwood, to provide food assistance to our Center Grove families in need. The CGCSC Food Service Department has purchased raw ground beef, peanut butter, applesauce, yogurt, cereal, chips, fresh produce, and strawberry cups that will be donated to the IMPACT Center and made available to our families. Here are the details:

WHAT: Food Assistance for Center Grove Families
WHERE: IMPACT Center at Mount Pleasant Christian Church
381 N Bluff Rd, Greenwood - southeast corner of the church lot
WHEN: Registration times: Thursdays, 9:15-9:40 a.m. and 6:15-6:40 p.m.; Saturdays, 9:15-9:40 a.m. (Please bring a valid ID to show proof of residency in Johnson County.)

We believe this plan will provide the greatest impact on our families. Any family in need, even those who have not been certified for Free/Reduced meals, may receive food assistance from the IMPACT Center distribution, as long as they live in Johnson County. More info: www.centergrove.k12.in.us/FreeResources.
